B. Decrease the set rate to 12bpm.
C. Decrease Fi02
D. Decrease the Vt to 500mL.
E. Start the SBT using either ASV 100%MV or CPAP/PS, notify the physician and RN and document in the EMR.

question_text: B.408 QP-Quality Management Plan PURPOSE: To provide an outline and description for the clinical program's Quality Management Program.  The Quality Management Program is structured to monitor processes and operations for quality management and improvement that include but are not limited to the following; donor and patient evaluation, selection and treatment, donor consent, recipient consent, emergency and safety procedures, donor and patient confidentiality, infection prevention and control, administration of the preparative regimen, transplantation of hematopoietic progenitor cells, use of immunosuppressive agents, growth factor administration, oral care, blood product transfusion, errors, accidents and adverse events, biological product deviations, corrective action plans, personnel training, competency assessment, HPC product and other cellular therapy product time to engraftment following product administration, outcome analysis, audits, facility maintenance and monitoring, disposal of medical biohazard waste, disaster response and agreement development and review for outside vendors/contract. The Blood and Marrow Transplant Program at Northside Hospital evaluates new patient consults, coordinates and organizes the pre/post-BMT evaluation/follow-up processes for both recipient/normal donor and ensures normal donors are FDA eligible and medically suitable and if not, required documentation and counseling has been performed. ---I have reviewed SOP B.408 QP-Quality Management Plan and all associated forms.

answer_text: a.	Send the care partner to get the car while you provide the patient with written discharge instructions and allow time for questions.

course_name: FY2021 CARE OF THE OLDER ADULT: NURSING
question_text: Which of the following is the best example of an effective discharge for an older adult patient:
answer_text: b.	At discharge, identify the patient's needs and follow up with the care coordinator. Complete the patient's discharge instructions with the care partner and patient present.

course_name: FY2021 CARE OF THE OLDER ADULT: NURSING
question_text: Which of the following is the best example of an effective discharge for an older adult patient:
answer_text: c.	The RN completes the discharge paperwork, allows adequate time for the patient to read instructions and performs teach-back.

course_name: FY2021 CARE OF THE OLDER ADULT: NURSING
question_text: Which of the following is the best example of an effective discharge for an older adult patient:
answer_text: d.	After assessing home needs throughout the stay, the RN communicates with the interdisciplinary team prior to discharge. A thorough reconciliation of medications and diet is performed prior to discharge. Education is done at the bedside with adequate lighting, providing the patient's glasses, and involving the family. Teach-back education is then provided to ensure patient and caregiver understanding.

course_name: FY2021 CARE OF THE OLDER ADULT: NURSING
question_text: The nurse is caring for a 70 year old male patient who has returned from surgery 1 hour ago. He is receiving NS @ 75/hr. Physical therapy has notified the RN to determine if they are ready to work with physical therapy. The RN assesses the patient's vitals: Temp 35.9C (96.5 F), HR 93, RR 18, BP 105/50, and Pulse ox 98% on 2 L NC. The patient reports their pain is a 5/10. The nurse's best response is to:
answer_text: a.	Let the patient know the plan to work with physical therapy and pre-medicate with morphine for pain.

question_text: The nurse is caring for a 70 year old male patient who has returned from surgery 1 hour ago. He is receiving NS @ 75/hr. The RN assesses the patient's vitals: Temp 35.9C (96.5 F), HR 93, RR 18, BP 105/50, and Pulse ox 98% on 2 L NC. The patient reports their pain is a 5/10. The nurse's best response is to:
answer_text: b.	Assess the patient including their cognitive status and any signs of orthostatic hypotension, review the patient's baseline vital signs. Defer physical therapy for now and provide a warm blanket. Monitor vitals more frequently. Administer acetaminophen prn pain.
